places.name: Courtyard Café
places.description: The Courtyard Café serves a range of fresh baguettes, turkish rolls, salads, pies, pastries and pasta, as well as a sandwich/salad bar where you can create your own lunchtime masterpiece. You can also grab coffee, tea and morning/afternoon tea snacks, and, if the mood takes you, even enjoy a glass of wine.

places.name: Footbridge Station
places.description: Looking for a new notepad, your favourite mag, bus tickets and a quick meal to grab and go? Footbridge Station is the Holme Building’s all-in-one newsagent, stationery shop and food outlet. It stocks delicious sandwiches, salads, pies, sausage rolls and cakes to go with our barista-made coffee and a broad range of University clothing, memorabilia and USU stationery.Sydney Morning Herald pick–up outlet and stocks kosher-certified food.

places.name: Manning Bar
places.description: Manning Bar provides a hub of leisure and entertainment on campus. It offerss a wide range of drinks, plenty of seating inside and on the balcony, regular entertainment and the legendary Manning Grill. Check the website and gig guides regulary to catch top international and local artists playing major sets all through the year.

places.name: Zabeli
places.description: Located on Level 1 of the Manning Building, Zabeli cafe offers a wide variety of foods, ranging from tasty pasta to delicious treats. Enjoy the great atmosphere and delicious food while you relax on the couches with friends.

places.name: Lettucehead
places.description: This groovy salad and sandwich bar located on the ground floor of the Manning Building serves great fresh food: scrumptious salads, yummy yoghurts, super–long baguette rolls stuffed with delicious fillings, superb sandwiches, mega meal deals and more.

places.name: Miso Honi
places.description: Great Asian fusion-style food. Stir-fries, steamed veggies, barbecued meats, classic fried rice and more. Grab a plate today!

places.name: Caffe Tra Baci
places.description: Caffe Tra Baci serves coffees, hot foods, delicious focaccias, gourmet bites and more. Grab a delicious banana bread, coffee and newspaper and kickstart your day. Sydney Morning Herald pick–up outlet

places.name: Manning Kiosk
places.description: An oasis for the hungry travellers of Manning Road. If you’re after a coffee on the go, or a quick bite, Manning Kiosk offers a wide selection of sandwiches, wraps, hot pastries, quiches, healthy fruit, delicious cakes, ice creams and snacks, both sweet and savoury.Sydney Morning Herald pick–up outlet

places.name: Snack Express
places.description: Snack Express is a convenient one–stop shop for lunch, snacks, coffee, confectionery, cold drinks and two of the best words you’ll ever hear on a hot day: frozen Coke. Stocks kosher-certified food.

places.name: Hermann's Bar
places.description: Nestled on the corner of Butlin Ave and City Road in the Wentworth Building, Hermann's is the University’s own hole-in-the-wall bar. Enjoy a top selection of beers, wines and spirits, with some must–try Hermann’s concoctions for good measure. When the weather’s good, sit out in the huge beer garden, if not, park up on one of the many comfy lounges inside. Wireless internet is available throughout the bar and there’s always something to enjoy, including lunchtime trivia, pool, sunset jazz and Project 52’s famous comedy nights – voted Sydney’s best comedy night in by Timeout Magazine in 2011.

places.name: Raw
places.description: For a healthier diet, Raw is the place to go.  Raw Health Bar offers a variety of healthy meal options and snacks such as freshly made salads, yogurts, gourmet rolls including gluten free options. Raw also serves a wide range of custom health juices and smoothies to quench a mighty thirst and add a boost to your day.

places.name: Cafe Azzuri (Wentworth)
places.description: Located on Level 1 of the Wentworth Building, the funky Café Azzuri has a reputation for awesome coffee and legendary brownies and burritos.

places.name: Uni Brothers Kebabs
places.description: We have made kebabs healthier. Our chicken is gluten free. Try our meatbox and veggie plates and our salads are delicious. All our food is made daily.

places.name: Jewel of India
places.description: Located in the Food Court on Level 2 of the Wentworth Building, the Jewel of India offers mouth–watering curries such as butter chicken, lamb, and hot beef vindaloo, along with many vegetarian delights, samosas, bhajis, fluffy naans, wraps, sweets and dips, all freshly prepared every day.

places.name: Bosch Catering Outlet
places.description: Located in the Bosch Lecture Theatre on Western Avenue, you can get your fill from a choice of gourmet sandwiches, foccaccias , fish and chips, burgers, cold drinks and coffee. We also provide an inside seating area.

places.name: Parma Cucina and Bar Shop
places.description: Located in the Bosch Lecture Theatre on Western Avenue, you can get your fill from a choice of gourmet sandwiches, foccaccias , fish and chips, burgers, cold drinks and coffee. We also provide an inside seating area.

places.name: Cafe Azzuri (JFR)
places.description: Located on Level 2 of  the Jane Foss Russell Building, Café Azzuri has great coffee, must- try French crepes – including nutella and banana – and one of Sydney's best Vietnamese pork rolls!

places.name: EasyWay Tea
places.description: Located in the Jane Foss Russell Plaza, EasyWay Tea is an international, multi-award-winning franchise specialising in tea, with an extensive range of unique tea-related beverages.

places.name: Engineering Café
places.description: Hunger is not a problem at the Engineering Café. It serves great lunch combos, big burgers, hot rolls as well as top quality coffees and on-the-go snacks. You can find it in the Peter Nicol Russell Building.

places.name: Fisher Coffee Cart
places.description: Fisher Coffee Cart is open seven days a week for barista-made coffee, snacks,  and cold drinks. Refresh yourself in between Fisher study stints. Serving coffee, snacks and quite tasty bites such as pies, sausage rolls and hot dogs, the Fisher Coffee Cart literally gives you food for thought.

places.name: Carslaw Coffee Cart
places.description: Conveniently located near the entrance of the Carslaw Building, Carslaw Coffee Cart is a handy one-stop shop for snacks, confectionery, cold drinks,pies, sausage rolls, hot dogs and barista-made coffee.

places.name: Mallett St Café
places.description: Based in the Sydney Nursing School, the Mallett Street Cafe serves a selection of all the snacks, sandwiches, confectionery, hot pastries, cold drinks and  coffee you need to get through the day.

places.name: Music Café
places.description: The Conservatorium of Music's Music Cafe is a handy one-stop shop for snacks, confectionery, cold drinks and barista-made coffee.

places.name: Music Bistro
places.description: The Conservatorium of Music’s Music Cafe is a handy one-stop shop for snacks, confectionery, cold drinks and barista-made coffee.

places.name: The Grandstand
places.description: The Grandstand Sports Bar and Function Centre is located in the Bruce Williams Pavilion on Number 1 Oval. The wide selection of drinks and mouth-watering menu offers something for everyone. Regular specials are available throughout the week.

places.name: The Forum Restaurant
places.description: This two-storey heritage residence houses a new contemporary restaurant with spacious timber terrace areas, cedar and glass-walled full-service indoor/outdoor restaurant and bar. The fully licensed  la carte restaurant is open for all-day dining.

places.name: The Downstairs Bar
places.description: An intimate bar opposite the Downstairs Theatre in the Seymour Centre, this is the perfect place for light pre-show snacks and post-show drinks. Each Thursday to Saturday it is transformed into the Sound Lounge, featuring live music.

places.name: The Everest Bar
places.description: With expansive floors and wall space, the Everest Bar in the Seymour Centre hosts regular exhibitions of sculpture and paintings, curated by Defiance Gallery in Newtown. It is the perfect bar for pre- and post-show functions and is a favourite for opening and closing night parties.

places.name: The Coffee Cart
places.description: Open before shows, the Coffee Cart serves great coffee, light snacks and alcoholic beverages. It is located in the main foyer opposite the Seymour Centre Box Office.

places.name: Ralph's cafe
places.description: Ralph's is renowned for serving great coffee and offers a wide selection of sandwiches and hot food. Staff are also available to cater functions.

places.name: The JDV Food Court
places.description: The perfect place to chill out and grab a bite to eat. The JDV Food Court has a food outlet to suit everyone.

places.name: Union Pharmacy
places.description: Located on Level 3 of the Wentworth Building, Union Pharmacy caters for all your healthcare needs. We offer a fast prescription service, cosmetics, fragances, vitamins and all daily essentials. Access discount is available on eligible products.

places.name: The Wentworth Campus Store
places.description: Find all your newsagency needs at the Campus Store on Level 3 of the Wentworth Building. Also stocks a wide range of University apparel, stationery and memorabilia. We also have all of your phone charge needs, and are the only Lotto agent on campus.

places.name: U Shop
places.description: Show your University allegiances, and  literally (almost) wear your heart on your sleeve! Located in the Jane Foss Russell Building, (City Rd), U Shop features exclusive University of Sydney branded merchandise; including wide range of hoodies, apparel, accessories, glassware, lab coats and souvenirs. We also offer children's and baby wear ranges for the next generation.

places.name: Academic Dress
places.description: On your big day, the friendly people at Academic Dress will transform you from student to fully fledged graduand with all the necessary regalia for sale and hire. To mark the occasion you can also find a wide selection of University memorabilia, fresh flowers, hoodies, apparel and giftware for all special occasions.

places.name: Westpac Bank (Sydney University Sport & Aquatic Centre)
Macleay Museum
places.description: The oldest museum of its kind in Australia, the Macleay Museum holds significant collections of ethnographic artefacts, scientific instruments, biological specimens and historic photographs.

places.name: Nicholson Museum
places.description: The Nicholson Museum contains the largest and most prestigious collection of antiquities in Australia.

places.name: Pathology Museum
places.description: Housing approximately 1600 pathological specimens, the museum originated in 1889 as The Museum of Normal and Morbid Anatomy. The most prized exhibit on display is a flask of broth prepared by Louis Pasteur for the culture of bacteria.

places.name: The Tin Sheds Gallery
places.description: The Tin Sheds Gallery is part of the Art Workshop complex in the Faculty of Architecture, Design and Planning. The gallery hosts exhibitions across a wide variety of contemporary visual arts practices from individuals and groups, as well as community projects and curated exhibitions.

places.name: University Art Gallery
places.description: The University Art Gallery contains more than 3000 works of art, including paintings, works on paper, sculpture and decorative arts, which have been acquired by donation and bequest since 1850.

places.name: Verge Gallery
places.description: The Verge Gallery is an exciting new addition to the University of Sydney campus, housing the best in unique and rousing student art.

places.name: Seymour Centre
places.description: The Seymour Centre presents a range of innovative musical and dramatic arts throughout the year. Its program includes dramatic and musical productions, public lectures (such as Sydney Ideas), the Sound Lounge live music venue, and student revues.

places.name: The Cellar
places.description: The Cellar Theatre is Sydney University Drama Society's (SUDS) very own performance space, hosting more than 16 productions each year.

places.name: Rare Books and Special Collections Library
Boundary Lane Children's Centre
places.description: Boundary Lane Children's Centre is located in Darlington, near the Wentworth Building. Its philosophy is to provide a high-quality child care service that fulfills the needs of the community and is accessible and affordable. It provides a happy, caring, stimulating, secure and bias-free environment for all children.

places.name: SDN Ngallia Children's Education and Care Centre
places.description: Ngallia Children's Education and Care Centre is based on the Cumberland Campus in Lidcombe. The centre's philosophy is to provide quality child care that is appropriate to the needs of children, parents or others responsible for each child. It actively promotes the education of the children in care by working in partnership with their families and other educators, and by extending the children's experiences, skills and knowledge.

places.name: Union Child Care Centre
places.description: Managed by KU Children's Services, and located in Darlington, the Union Child Care Centre's primary aim is to create an environment which is caring and family–like, striving to nurture and stimulate children through play experiences, based on the children's individual strengths and interests.

places.name: Laurel Tree House
places.description: Managed by KU Children's Services, and located in Glebe, Laurel Tree House is committed to providing a caring, educational and nurturing environment which meets the diverse educational and developmental needs of all children. The centre strives to enhance children's strengths and abilities to learn, while assisting families to support their children's wellbeing and development.

places.name: Carillon Avenue Child Care Centre
places.description: Managed by KU Children's Services, Carillon Avenue Child Care Centre is located in Newtown. The centre's primary aim is to create a home-like atmosphere through a loving, stable, secure and responsive environment in which each child can grow and develop to their fullest potential. Each child is seen as an individual with his/her own interests, strengths and needs in life.

Ultimately, Adore life focuses on preventive healthcare for you to increase the quality of your life.
